Only the Resonance Parameter Covariance file(RPCM) was given in   2525 1451
ORNL 2007-2008 evaluation.  The uncertainties on the group        2525 1451
capture cross sections calculated from this RPCM were about 0.8%  2525 1451
at thermal energies and about 0.6-1.3% in the high energy groups  2525 1451
The uncertainties in the high energy ranges are obviously too     2525 1451
small, compared to those in the table above, as it was pointed out2525 1451
by P. Oblozinsky and C. Mattoon(2009)                             2525 1451
The RPCM was recalculated and a new file 32 was created           2525 1451
containing the uncertainties and covariances of the parameters    2525 1451
generated only from the stastistical uncertainties of the         2525 1451
experimental data base. The systematic uncertainties were         2525 1451
estimated from results obtained in the SAMMY analysis of the      2525 1451
experimental data base, from some information found in the        2525 1451
publications, and from discussion with some authors.  The cross   2525 1451
section covariance files 33001, 33002, and 33102 were then        2525 1451
obtained. The new ENDF file, processed by PUFF-IV, gave group     2525 1451
cross section uncertainties varying from 0.8% at 0.0253 eV to     2525 1451
7.4% at 10 eV, when the previous evaluations(ORNL and BNL) gave   2525 1451
a constant value of 0.8% below 10 eV. The calculated capture      2525 1451
cross section at 10 eV is about 0.5 b. The capture cross section  2525 1451
has been measured by Widder in the energy range 0.01 eV to 10 eV  2525 1451
with 4.2%, 1.9%, 5% accuracy at energies 0.01 eV, 0.0253 eV,10 eV 2525 1451
respectively, close to the values given in the present work.      2525 1451
